description: A WEBBOOKMARK file is a bookmarks file saved with Appleâ€™s Safari web browser on macOS. It contains informaiton about the webpage that user has saved from the browser. Information stored in a WEBBOOKMARK file includes the page title, URL, and the bookmark group to which this page is stored. When a webpage is bookmarked, Safari browser asks the group for storing the bookmarked page. Most users save the bookmarks in Bookmarks folder which is the default location offered by common browsers.
